  "body": "* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\nDefault Configuration puts prometheus annotations at the deployment-leve of the rook-ceph-mgr pod, which won't get picked up by \"default\" prometheus-config.\r\n\r\n```\r\napiVersion: extensions/v1beta1\r\nkind: Deployment\r\nmetadata:\r\n  annotations:\r\n    ...\r\n    prometheus.io/port: \"9283\"\r\n    prometheus.io/scrape: \"true\"\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nAnnotation should be either in the pod-template or at the service-level for prometheus to scrape all the pods or only the service.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n- deploy prometheus with example-config from https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus/blob/master/documentation/examples/prometheus- kubernetes.yml\r\n- deploy default rook-v1.0.1\r\n- prometheus wont scrape rook-ceph-mgr\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration: bare-metal\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod): v1.0.1\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.13.5\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift): Rancher2\r\n* Storage backend status (e.g. for Ceph use `ceph health` in the [Rook Ceph toolbox](https://rook.io/docs/rook/master/ceph-toolbox.html)): HEALTH_OK\r\n\r\nregards,\r\nRoman",
